| Who submits the request? | Community resident | Behavior Fact | Primary user |
| What is the core entity? | Repair request | Data Fact | Entity mapping |
| What must happen after submit? | The workflow returns category and handler suggestion before the user confirms dispatch. | Workflow Rule | Primary loop |
| What is the implementation limit? | Local prototype only; no external notification channel. | Concrete Constraint | Out of scope |
| How do we know it works? | A user can submit a repair request and see a suggestion. | Acceptance Fact | Acceptance check |
| Should it support advanced analytics? | Nice to have after the primary loop works. | Attitude / Wish | Keep out of V1 |
| Is the property system API available? | Unknown. | Unknown | Use mock fallback |

## Assumptions

| Assumption | Reason | Risk if Wrong |
|------------|--------|---------------|
| Single demo account is enough | Local prototype | Add login flow later |

## Product Shape

- Target app type: PC backend/admin app.
- First screen after login: dashboard with repair workbench entry.
- Required workbench surfaces: dashboard, list, form, detail.
- Explicitly not building: marketing page, mobile app, chat-only page, pure report page.

## Requirements Baseline

- Primary user: community resident
- Primary loop: resident submits a repair request and receives an AI-generated triage suggestion
- Core entity: repair request
- Core states: pending, assigned, closed
- Workflow input: request description
- Workflow output: triage category and suggested handler
- Acceptance check: a resident can submit a request and see a suggestion
- Out of scope: real notification channels, multi-tenant auth

## Baseline Classification

| Baseline Field | Evidence | Answer Type | Risk / Follow-up |
|----------------|----------|-------------|------------------|
| Primary user | Community resident submits a repair request | Behavior Fact | If staff enters requests, role changes |
| Primary loop | Submit request, receive workflow suggestion, confirm dispatch | Workflow Rule | Dispatch handling is limited |
| Core entity | Repair request fields and state | Data Fact | Attachment upload is out of scope |
| Core states | pending, assigned, closed | Workflow Rule | More states can be added later |
| Workflow input | request description | Data Fact | Real platform fields may differ |
| Workflow output | triage category and suggested handler | Data Fact | Mock must match real envelope |
| Acceptance check | user can submit and see a suggestion | Acceptance Fact | Browser verification still needed after implementation |
| Out of scope | no external notifications or multi-tenant auth | Concrete Constraint | Add in later phase |
| Nice-to-have analytics | future preference | Attitude / Wish | Do not freeze as V1 |
| Property system API | no source available | Unknown | Use mock fallback |

## Primary Loop

1. Resident logs in.
2. Resident opens the repair create page.
3. Resident enters a description and submits.
4. App calls the AI workflow adapter.
5. App displays the triage suggestion.

## Acceptance Checks

- [ ] App is recognizably a PC backend/admin app.
- [ ] Primary loop works end-to-end locally.
- [ ] AI workflow adapter has a mock fallback with the same response shape.
- [ ] docs/requirements/solution-options.md records 3 options and the selected option before implementation.
- [ ] README documents run command, URL, and demo account if any.
- [ ] \`bin/check-demo .\` passes.

## Out of Scope

- Multi-tenant authentication.
- External notification channels.
`,
    'docs/requirements/solution-options.md': `# Solution Options

## Requirements Baseline Reference

