    'docs/technical/workflow-integration.md': `# Workflow Integration

## Role
The AI workflow classifies repair requests and returns a suggested action.

## Business Workflow Endpoint

\`POST /api/repairs/triage\`

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Page route | /repair/create |
| Business API endpoint | /api/repairs/triage |
| Method | POST |
| Called from UI file | templates/repair/create.html |

## Adapter Location
\`workflow_adapter.py\`

## Request Shape
\`\`\`json
{ "input": "string" }
\`\`\`

## Response Shape
\`\`\`json
{ "ok": true, "data": { "category": "string", "handler": "string" }, "error": null, "fallback": true }
\`\`\`

## Mock Fallback
When the AI platform is unavailable, the app returns a mock response with the same shape.

## Error Handling
| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Invalid input | Return 400 with error envelope and code INVALID_INPUT |
| Timeout | Return mock fallback and log warning |
| Empty result | Return success envelope with empty flag |
| Platform error | Return mock fallback with same shape and log error |

## Configuration
| Name | Default | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| WORKFLOW_MOCK | true | Use mock response |
| WORKFLOW_TIMEOUT | 10 | Real call timeout |

## Switching to Real Workflow
Set WORKFLOW_MOCK=false and implement _call_real_workflow.

## Readiness Probe
\`\`\`bash
DEMO_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5000 DEMO_PRIMARY_LOOP_PATH=/repair/create DEMO_BUSINESS_API_PATH=/api/repairs/triage DEMO_BUSINESS_API_PAYLOAD='{"input":"楼道灯坏了"}' ./bin/check-demo .
\`\`\`

## Test Examples
\`\`\`bash
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/repairs/triage -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"input":"楼道灯坏了"}'
